														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2084631">
									

<p>A minor point, but 399 definitely wouldn't be mild, if such a classification class existed. It would be trivially easy to kill someone with it.</p>
<p>Edit: This is a good segue into the other major problem with this proposals. More levels will equal more debate over which level something should be put into.</p>
<p>But I do agree that if the Foundation or something like it were real, this is closer to the classification system they'd use. Probably they'd use some sort of alpha-numeric system specifying both the level of threat and giving some indication as to the type of threat e.g. &quot;5C&quot; might mean a level five threat, caused by cognitohazardous effects.</p>

							</div>

								
