<p>In theory *hides from the incoming storm* it could work in cannon. The documents shown are detailed, but are usually a quick read. So for the uber-detailed stuff (like putting them into file folders at O5 command or whatever it is) it could have the different sub classes.<br />
The S/E/K system gives the reader (in-universe, a researcher/agent) just enough info to see: S=just don't mess with it and you're good, E=a little more work needs to go into containing/understanding this K=ALL RESOURCES GO INTO KEEPING THIS IN A LOCKED BOX AS FAR FROM HUMANS AS POSSIBLE<br />
Bonus:<br />
Appolyon: been nice serving with ya<br />
Thaumiel: anti-thingy</p>
<p>Edit: I didn't think through what commenting on a (roughly) three year old article would do. I am sorry.</p>

